						<div class="postbody">update here and i come for any input i can get. We found a much better datasheet and were able to decipher some information from the conexant xbox  and even some values. <br /><br />First here is the datasheet with the values: <br /><br />Please someone correct me if im wrong but i was able to decipher this for 240p for values to enter in our nkpatcher for xbox:<br /><br />NTSC<br />db 0x38, 0x76, 0x78, 0x7A, 0x7C, 0x7E, 0x80, 0x82, 0x84, 0x86, 0x88 0x8A ; register<br />db 0x40, 0xE0, 0x80, 0x94, 0xB0, 0x78, 0x09, 0x42, 0xCA, 0x27, 0x00 0xD0 ; 240p<br /><br />These values can be put in the nkpatcher.asm in the nkpatcher source linked below in the link. Here is the snippet with the original code we are trying to replace:<br /><br />conexantregs:<br />	db 0xD6, 0x2E, 0x32, 0x3C, 0x3E, 0x40, 0xC4, 0xC6, 0xCE, 0xA0, 0x9E, 0x9C, 0x6C ; register<br />	db 0x0C, 0x00, 0x48, 0x80, 0x80, 0x80, 0x01, 0x98, 0xE1, 0x8C, 0x00, 0x00, 0x46 ; 480p<br />	db 0x0C, 0x00, 0x48, 0x80, 0x80, 0x80, 0x01, 0x98, 0xE1, 0x21, 0x00, 0x00, 0x46 ; 720p<br />	db 0x0C, 0x00, 0x48, 0x80, 0x80, 0x80, 0x01, 0x98, 0xE1, 0x21, 0x00, 0x00, 0x46 ; 1080i<br />.end<br /><br />Using this nkpatcher we have tried this and so far, efforts have resulted in a black screen. However im posting the link to the nkpatcher source i am working with to see if theres anything we might be missing. Hopefully someone will see something we might be missing. <br /><br /><!-- m --><a class="postlink" href="http://www.qfpost.com/links.do?get=662e67d6afaea07cd6f583598ca59b13">http://www.qfpost.com/links.do?get=662e ... 598ca59b13</a><!-- m --><br /><br />Its real easy to compile with this download. You just make whatever changes you want to make to the source then click make_nkp11.bat to make an xbe. <br /><br />We can only see 2 autoconfigs for NTSC, and theres 2 for pal, 320x240 config, and 320x200. Hope to hear if anyone more talented than us sees something.</div>

					
