					<td>
					

						<div class="postbody">Decided to pull this back up and see if anyone here with any experience in the matter can offer some assistance or guidance on the actual hardware side or anyone who understands encoder can help. <br /><br />First i made some notes after studying the conexant encoders datasheet. This comes directly from the conexant encoders datasheet itself:<br /><br />1. The vertical scaling can be disabled by setting the internal<br />V_SCALE register to 4096 for a non-interlaced input.<br /><br />section 1.3.18 Standard<br />Flicker Filtering<br /><br />Other CX25870 registers and bits must<br />be reprogrammed to generate different video outputs. The bits in Table 1-18 are the most important settings<br /><br />Figure 1-17. Noninterlaced 262-Line (NTSC) Video Timing<br /><br /><br />1.3.33 Noninterlaced Output<br /><br />When the CX25870/871 is programmed for noninterlaced video out via the NI_OUT bit, it always transmits the odd field. The FIELD pin will continue to change state on the leading edge of the<br />analog vertical sync. A 30 Hz offset should be subtracted from the color subcarrier frequency<br />while in NTSC mode so that the color subcarrier phase is inverted from field to field. The transition from interlaced to noninterlaced in master interface occurs during odd fields to prevent<br />synchronization disturbance.<br /><br />Question, Could something like this be done through a more simpler means of not using a direct program or maybe something like hex editing?<br /><br />Also i know this was brought up before but this:  <!-- m --><a class="postlink" href="http://sourceforge.net/projects/nv-tv-out/files/?source=navbar">http://sourceforge.net/projects/nv-tv-o ... rce=navbar</a><!-- m --> has a link to use this program through xbox linux, but i have no means of getting this to work as everything i have tried is not working, but in the files there is a program for xbox for this.</div>

